<sub>CI matrix: Python 3.9‚Äì3.12 √ó NumPy 1.x and 2.x</sub>

<sub>Patent pending: U.S. Provisional 63/897,572 (filed 2025‚Äë10‚Äë11). See <a href="PATENTS.md">PATENTS.md</a>.</sub>

Setup: synthetic ‚Äúfacts + traps‚Äù dataset ‚Äî see the notebook for N, k, trials, seed. Reproducible via `notebooks/04_hallucination_reduction.ipynb`. Traps flagged; gate=0.01, off‚Äëtopic damp=0.5.

- ‚ö° Inverse scaling: latency often decreases as corpus size grows (<40 ms at N‚âà1200 CPU). For fixed D, k, and CG tol, settle tends to stay ~constant or improve with denser graphs. [scaling chart](assets/benchmarks/scale_timing.png) ¬∑ [run](scripts/scale_benchmark.py)
- üéØ Hallucinations: 42.9% ‚Üí 0% in a controlled study[1]. See the notebook (N, k, trials, seed). [study](notebooks/04_hallucination_reduction.ipynb) ¬∑ [CLI sample](assets/benchmarks/competitor_single.png) ¬∑ [run](scripts/competitor_benchmark.py)
- üßæ Receipts: SHA‚Äë256 state signature; optional HMAC‚ÄëSHA256. [schema](docs/RECEIPTS.md)
- üîß Universal: works with any embeddings, no retraining. [adapters](#adapters--model-compatibility) ¬∑ [quickstart](examples/quickstart.py)
- üìà Self‚Äëoptimizing: learns parameters over time. [adaptive suite](scripts/bench_adaptive_suite.py)
- üöÄ Production: scales to millions. [perf snapshot](scripts/perf_snapshot.py) ¬∑ [scale](scripts/scale_benchmark.py)

